me.alb_i986.selenium.tinafw.domain

Class Browser

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.alb_i986.selenium.tinafw.domain.Browser

  • public class Browser
extends Object
    A Browser can be opened and closed, and can be used to browse to some page. It is backed by a WebDriver: by opening a Browser, a WebDriver is instantiated.

    It relies on a WebDriverFactory for instantiating WebDrivers. The factory may be injected in the constructor. See Browser() for details on the default factory.

    A Browser has a type, one of SupportedBrowser. The type is not bound to an instance of Browser: it is chosen when opening the browser. Thus, a Browser instance, during its life, may represent many different types of browsers (one for each pair of calls to open(SupportedBrowser) and close()).
